description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated individual to join our team of nurses working within our busy endoscopy departments which is currently working towards achieving JAG accreditation. If you are eager to learn, have a flexible approach to work, reliable and enthusiastic, we would like to hear from you. You should be a Registered Nurse with extensive skills and commitment to continuing professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be Based in Singleton Endoscopy Unit however will rotate to service needs to the other Swansea Units At Singleton and Neath Port Talbot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shift Patterns will be over 7 days with potential weekend and Bank holiday working and in the future take part in an on call rota at Morriston Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous Endoscopy experience is not required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 17/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Rhian Wheatley&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Unit Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: rhian.wheatley@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
